.el .ds Aq '
.TH devin-mcp-add 1  "add " 
.SH NAME
devin\-mcp\-add \- Add a new MCP server
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdevin mcp add\fR [\fB\-t\fR|\fB\-\-transport\fR] [\fB\-s\fR|\fB\-\-scope\fR] [\fB\-\-url\fR] [\fB\-\-command\fR] [\fB\-e\fR|\fB\-\-env\fR] [\fB\-H\fR|\fB\-\-header\fR] [\fB\-\-scopes\fR] [\fB\-\-oauth\-client\-id\fR] [\fB\-\-oauth\-client\-secret\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fINAME\fR> [\fIPOSITIONAL_URL\fR] [\fIARGS\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Add a new MCP server.
.PP
Transport is inferred automatically when \-\-transport is omitted: \- If a URL is provided (positional or \-\-url) → HTTP \- If \-\-command is provided or trailing args (after \-\-) are present → stdio
.PP
For stdio servers, \-\-command is optional when trailing args are provided; the first trailing arg becomes the command and the rest become its arguments.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-transport\fR \fI<TRANSPORT>\fR
Transport type (inferred when omitted: URL → http, trailing args → stdio)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
stdio: Standard input/output (local process)
.IP \(bu 2
sse: Server\-Sent Events (HTTP streaming)
.IP \(bu 2
http: HTTP request/response
.RE
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-scope\fR \fI<SCOPE>\fR [default: local]
Configuration scope
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
local: Local project config, not committed (.devin/config.local.json)
.IP \(bu 2
project: Project\-level config (.devin/config.json)
.IP \(bu 2
user: User\-level config (~/.config/devin/config.json)
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-url\fR \fI<URL>\fR
URL for HTTP/SSE transports (alternative to positional URL)
.TP
\fB\-\-command\fR \fI<COMMAND>\fR
Command for stdio transport (optional when trailing args are provided)
.TP
\fB\-e\fR, \fB\-\-env\fR \fI<KEY=VALUE>\fR
Environment variables

Format: KEY=value. Can be specified multiple times.
.TP
\fB\-H\fR, \fB\-\-header\fR \fI<HEADER: VALUE>\fR
HTTP headers

Format: "Header: value". Can be specified multiple times.
.TP
\fB\-\-scopes\fR \fI<SCOPE,SCOPE>\fR
OAuth scopes to request (comma\-separated)

Only used for HTTP/SSE servers that support OAuth.
.TP
\fB\-\-oauth\-client\-id\fR \fI<ID>\fR
Pre\-registered OAuth client ID for servers that don\*(Aqt support dynamic client registration (e.g. GitHub)
.TP
\fB\-\-oauth\-client\-secret\fR \fI<SECRET>\fR
OAuth client secret (for confidential clients)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fINAME\fR>
Server name
.TP
[\fIPOSITIONAL_URL\fR]
URL (positional, for HTTP/SSE transports)

Can also be provided via \-\-url. When both are given, \-\-url takes precedence.
.TP
[\fIARGS\fR]
Arguments for stdio command

Pass arguments after \-\- at the end of the command. When \-\-command is omitted, the first argument is used as the command.
